    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen using vim.diagnostic.config's `signs.numl` + `cursorline` + `cursorlineopt=number`, it's easy to lose track of what's the current line, because the diagnostic highlight has a higher priority. Example:\n\n<img width=\"166\" height=\"282\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/16c6912d-6f13-4904-9836-e5cd8b2c5490\" />\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n~Add a new config field to vim.diagnostic.config, akin to `sign_define()`'s [`culhl`](https://neovim.io/doc/user/vimfn/#sign_define()) key (could define some default highlight groups...).~\n\n- Add a new field to `nvim_buf_set_extmark`, to set the highlight group for the numberline on the current line (`cursorline_num_hl_group`?)\n- Add a new config field to `vim.diagnostic.config` to set said highlight groups\n\nAlternatively, could combine highlight groups on the statuscolumn (related https://github.com/vim/vim/issues/16842).",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Okay, as it turns out, `culhl` affects only the signcolumn. vim.diagnostic's signs are implemented with extmarks, which have `cursorline_hl_group` with the same limitation. It looks like there's no way to override a highlight group for the numbercolumn, for the current line only (aka `culnumhl` or `cursorline_num_hl_group`). So I guess this is actually a feature request to `nvim_buf_set_extmark` 🫣",
            "created_at": "2026-05-15T23:57:24Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/39799#issuecomment-4464606100",
